    <p> A few weeks ago I decided to go from the hostel to Manly with some beliefs. Manly is a district of Sydney, which borders directly on the sea in the northeast and has many beaches. Not only to the open sea but also towards the port. There we absolutely wanted to walk through the Haitunnel to Manly's best -known beach and in the Sealife Aquarium Manly. </p>
    <p> The easiest way to get to Manly from the city center is by ferry. This drives off between the Harbor Bridge and the opera house on such a Gennanten Circular Quay. On this day we also had nice weather and even a cruise ship in the harbor. So you can imagine that I have already taken countless photos on the way to Manly. </p>
    <p> When we arrived in Manly, we went straight to the Sealife Aquarium along a small but fine and well -lived beach. </p>
    <p> Unfortunately, some beach access was closed. When we read the signs we couldn't believe the reason for the blocking. The signs said that the access is partially blocked because penguins are breeding there. I have to say that this piece of beach is not a way away from the beach in the middle of nature but is a jetty for a harbor ferry operating in a 30 -minute clock. </p>
