    <p> There are also tens of surf, paddle and sailing schools as well as a small marina. The city starts right next to the beach. On the investor, thousands of people joined every day and even the usual suspects such as Mc Donalds, Subway and Aldi are represented directly on the investor. Definitely no place where you can suspect breeding penguins. We found it absolutely unimaginable. </p>
    <p> There was also a small group of penguins in the aquarium and how we learned from a friendly employee. They are called that because they are only 30cm the smallest kind of penguins and secondly their plumage shimmers blue in the sun. This colony is the last here in the state. Until recently there was a second bigger one. If I remember correctly, here too in Sydney. However, this was wiped out by a single dog. </p>
    <p> After we had made ourselves smart about the penguins, who lived on the upper floor we continued through the aquarium. There were several artificial coral reef on the ground floor in which many colorful fish and corals live. We were lucky enough to feed some of these fish and to learn a lot again. For example, we learned that some of these fish and octopuses have dark lights or green blood and three hearts. But what was much more impressive was the fact that this fish that I have so often admired in aquariums in Germany are at home here. One more reason to drive to the Great Barrier Reef. </p>
